stry causes.\"\n| <ref>{{cite web|title=Winners & Nominees 1969 \u2013 Golden Globes|url=https://www.goldenglobes.com/winners-nominees/1969|website=The Golden Globes|publisher=[[Hollywood Foreign Press Association]]|accessdate=January 18, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[27th Golden Globe Awards|1970]]\n| [[File:Joan Crawford - 1936 - Hurrell.JPG|100px|alt=Joan Crawford in 1936]]\n! scope=\"row\"| {{sort|Crawford|[[Joan Crawford]]}}\n| {{flag|USA}}\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| \"From 1925 and throughout the '60s, she was the reigning queen of the Hollywood filmscape.\"\n| <ref>{{cite web|title=Winners & Nominees 1970 \u2013 Golden Globes|url=https://www.goldenglobes.com/winners-nominees/1970|website=The Golden Globes|publisher=[[Hollywood Foreign Press Association]]|accessdate=January 18, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[28th Golden Globe Awards|1971]]\n| [[File:Frank Sinatra, 1959.jpg|100px|alt=Frank Sinatra in 1959]]\n! scope=\"row\"| {{sort|Sinatra|[[Frank Sinatra]]}}\n| {{flag|USA}}\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| \"A singing/acting legend, loved and revered by countless fans all over the world.\"\n| <ref>{{cite web|title=Winners & Nominees 1971 \u2013 Golden Globes|url=https://www.goldenglobes.com/winners-nominees/1971|website=The Golden Globes|publisher=[[Hollywood Foreign Press Association]]|accessdate=January 18, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[29th Golden Globe Awards|1972]]\n| [[File:Alfred Hitchcock NYWTS.jpg|100px|alt=Alfred Hitchcock in 1956]]\n! scope=\"row\"| {{sort|Hitchcock|[[Alfred Hitchcock]]}}\n| {{flag|UK}}\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| \"Hailed as the unmatched master of the thriller genre, first during his so-called British period, then in American films.\"\n| <ref>{{cite web|title=Winners & Nominees 1972 \u2013 Golden Globes|url=https://www.goldenglobes.com/winners-nominees/1972|website=The Golden Globes|publisher=[[Hollywood Foreign Press Association]]|accessdate=January 18, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[30th Golden Globe Awards|1973]]\n| [[File:Samuel Goldwyn - Jul 1919 EH.jpg|