lisher=[[Hollywood Foreign Press Association]]|accessdate=January 18, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[63rd Golden Globe Awards|2006]]\n| [[File:Anthony Hopkins-Tuscan Sun Festival.jpg|100px|alt=Anthony Hopkins in 2009]]\n! scope=\"row\"| {{sort|Hopkins|[[Anthony Hopkins]]}}\n| {{flag|UK}}\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| \"His reserved character and personality belie his explosive energy on screen and his outstanding power of expression.\"\n| <ref>{{cite web|title=Winners & Nominees 2006 \u2013 Golden Globes|url=https://www.goldenglobes.com/winners-nominees/2006|website=The Golden Globes|publisher=[[Hollywood Foreign Press Association]]|accessdate=January 18, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[64th Golden Globe Awards|2007]]\n| [[File:Warren Beatty - 1975.JPG|100px|alt=Warren Beatty in Shampoo (1975)]]\n! scope=\"row\"| {{sort|Beatty|[[Warren Beatty]]}}\n| {{flag|USA}}\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| \"One of the most fascinating characters in the history of Hollywood, Warren Beatty received five Golden Globes, including one as [[Golden Globe Award for Best Actor \u2013 Motion Picture Musical or Comedy|Best Actor (Comedy or Musical)]] for ''[[Heaven Can Wait (1978 film)|Heaven Can Wait]]'' and another as [[Golden Globe Award for Best Director|Best Director]] for ''[[Reds (film)|Reds]]''.\"\n| <ref>{{cite web|title=Winners & Nominees 2007 \u2013 Golden Globes|url=https://www.goldenglobes.com/winners-nominees/2007|website=The Golden Globes|publisher=[[Hollywood Foreign Press Association]]|accessdate=January 18, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[65th Golden Globe Awards|2008]]\n! colspan=\"4\" scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:center;\" | {{sort|ZZ|Not awarded}}{{efn|The 2008 awards ceremony was cancelled due to the [[2007\u201308 Writers Guild of America strike]]; the HFPA deferred the award to the 2009 ceremony.<ref name=\"2008 writer's strike\">{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/entertainment/7179401.stm|work=[[BBC News]]|title=Spielberg Globe honour 'deferred'|date=January 9, 2008|accessdate=Jan