|accessdate=January 18, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[68th Golden Globe Awards|2011]]\n| [[File:Robert De Niro 2011 Shankbone.JPG|100px|alt=Robert De Niro in 2011]]\n! scope=\"row\"| {{sort|De Niro|[[Robert De Niro]]}}\n| {{flag|USA}}\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| \"An actors' actor, from ''[[Mean Streets]]'' and ''[[The Godfather Part II]]'' to ''[[Silver Linings Playbook]]'' and ''[[Joy (film)|Joy]]''. Nominated for eight Golden Globes, winner as [[Golden Globe Award for Best Actor \u2013 Motion Picture Drama|Best Actor/Drama]] for ''[[Raging Bull]]''.\"\n| <ref>{{cite web|title=Winners & Nominees 2011 \u2013 Golden Globes|url=https://www.goldenglobes.com/winners-nominees/2011|website=The Golden Globes|publisher=[[Hollywood Foreign Press Association]]|accessdate=January 18, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[69th Golden Globe Awards|2012]]\n| [[File:Academy Award-winning actor Morgan Freeman narrates for the opening ceremony (26904746425) (cropped).jpg|100px|alt=Morgan Freeman in 2016]]\n! scope=\"row\"| {{sort|Freeman|[[Morgan Freeman]]}}\n| {{flag|USA}}\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| \"A stellar career spanning over forty years in film, stage and television. One of the most respected figures in the entertainment industry.\"\n| <ref>{{cite web|title=Winners & Nominees 2012 \u2013 Golden Globes|url=https://www.goldenglobes.com/winners-nominees/2012|website=The Golden Globes|publisher=[[Hollywood Foreign Press Association]]|accessdate=January 18, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[70th Golden Globe Awards|2013]]\n| [[File:Jodie Foster C\u00e9sars 2011 2 (cropped).jpg|100px|alt=Jodie Foster in 2011]]\n! scope=\"row\"| {{sort|Foster|[[Jodie Foster]]}}\n| {{flag|USA}}\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| \"From child actor to movie star and beyond: director, producer, industry leader. Her acceptance speech at 70th Golden Globe Awards became one of the highlights of the evening.\"\n| <ref>{{cite web|title=Winners & Nominees 2013 \u2013 Golden Globes|url=https://www.goldenglobes.com/winners-nominees/2013|web